sentence: Consumer stocks easily outpaced most other sectors today despite giving back a small portion of their prior gains, with shares of consumer staples companies in the S&P 500 rising nearly 0.9% while shares of consumer discretionary firms in the S&P 500 were adding over 0.6% in value today.

In company news, Procter & Gamble ( PG ) was helping to keep the Dow Jones Industrial Average on positive ground this afternoon, with the consumer products conglomerate rising over 1% today after this morning reporting fiscal Q4 net income and sales beating analyst estimates.

The company earned $0.85 per share during the three months ended June 30, up from $0.79 per share during the same period last year and also coming in ahead of the $0.78 per share Capital IQ consensus.
Revenue slipped 0.1% from year-ago levels to $16.08 billion, also exceeding the Street view by around $70 million.
The company is expecting growth of between 5% to 7% in its FY18 core earnings per share.
(+) NAKD, Acquires 100% ownership of FOH Online Corp., the exclusive Frederick's of Hollywood global licensee.
Financial terms of the transaction with Bendon Ltd. were not disclosed.
(-) SAVE, Adjusted Q2 EPS of $1.14 exceeds analyst consensus by $0.04 per share.
Revenue rises 20.1% over last year to $701.68 mln, roughly in-line with the $702.29 mln consensus.
